i used velvet pouch for S8. I treated the S8 like a precious and sensitive historical monument. But as a result, scratches occurred on the screen in 3 days. As the rules of physics say. It doesn't matter if the glass is harder than your finger. Since the surface area of the powder or skin piece that goes between the finger and the screen, which you cannot see, is very small, it will became as hard as diamond. It is like the water showing concrete effect when it is too high. Or like a drop of water dripping through the rocks. Every time you touch your finger on the screen, even if only a few atoms leave the surface, the screen will inevitably be damaged with sufficient time.
